New Zealand's inflation rate decline balance payment improve significantly fiscal March 1988 Institute Economic Research (NZIER) said. The independent institute quarterly March issue revise fiscal 1987 real gross domestic product (GDP) forecast fall 0.5 pct pct drop forecast December. Government figure show GDP grow annual 1.8 pct quarter September 3.4 pct June quarter. The NZIER sharp improvement June September quarter due mainly tax structure introduction 10 pct value-added good service tax expect continue half 1986/87. The government's tight fiscal position expect change said. Annual inflation measure consumer price index forecast fall nine pct March 18.2 pct calendar 1986 said. "Falling inflation likely significant scope reduction nominal rates; real rate expect ease (albeit slightly) balance payment deficit hence call overseas capital fall away" NZIER said. Short-term rate forecast remain 20 25 pct June quarter decline half 1987/88 16 18 pct. Long-term rate expect fall 14 16 pct. Five government bond rate currently 18.40 pct key indicator 30-day bank bill 26.53 pct. The local dollar expect depreciate steadily come March reach 57.5 Reserve Bank's trade weight index base basket currencies. The index stand 66.4. "A marked improvement balance payment forecast" NZIER said. "The current account deficit expect fall 7.5 pct GDP 1985/86 4.5 pct 1986/87 2.5 pct 1987/88." The current account deficit forecast shrink 1.32 billion N.Z. Dlrs 1987/88 2.40 billion 1986/87 3.33 billion 1985/86. The 1987/88 budget deficit forecast 2.8 billion dlrs expect 2.9 billion dlrs 1986/87 1.87 billion 1985/86. This compare government's 1986/87 deficit figure 2.92 billion earlier forecast 2.45 billion. "Conditions come sufficiently subdue contribute marked improvement balance payment rate inflation ..." NZIER said. "Overall significant gain New Zealand economy continue improve bode future prospects." REUTER 